File: Rugby players seen in a scrum with a rugby ball. AFP/Meg Oliphant/Getty Images JOHANNESBURG - Former Border Bulldogs coach Elliot Fana has died in a car accident. Fana coached World Cup winners Lukhanyo Am and Makazole Mapimpi. Before taking up rugby coaching permanently, Fana mentored Proteas Test captain Dean Elgar at St Dominic’s College in Welkom.
Between 2008 and 2011, he was an SA Under-20 technical coach. READ: Defiant Jones confident he can oversee England revival at World Cup Springboks Elton Jantjies, Patrick Lambie, Jaco Taute, and as Francois Venter were part of that team at the time. He also coached Ireland international CJ Stander. Fana was the director of rugby at Fort Hare at the time of his passing.